theorem
(G is_metric_of A iff (G is  Reflexive  discerning & (for a,b,c being (Element of A) holds ( G . (b,c) ) <= ( ( G . (a,b) ) + ( G . (a,c) ) ))))
proof
A1: ((G is  Reflexive  discerning & (for a,b,c being (Element of A) holds ( G . (b,c) ) <= ( ( G . (a,b) ) + ( G . (a,c) ) ))) implies G is_metric_of A)
proof
assume that
A2: G is  Reflexive  discerning
and
A3: (for a,b,c being (Element of A) holds ( G . (b,c) ) <= ( ( G . (a,b) ) + ( G . (a,c) ) ));
A4: (for b,c being (Element of A) holds ( G . (b,c) ) = ( G . (c,b) ))
proof
let b being (Element of A),c being (Element of A);
( G . (c,b) ) <= ( ( G . (b,c) ) + ( G . (b,b) ) ) by A3;
then A5: ( G . (c,b) ) <= ( ( G . (b,c) ) + ( 0 ) ) by A2,METRIC_1:def 2;
( G . (b,c) ) <= ( ( G . (c,b) ) + ( G . (c,c) ) ) by A3;
then ( G . (b,c) ) <= ( ( G . (c,b) ) + ( 0 ) ) by A2,METRIC_1:def 2;
hence thesis by A5,XXREAL_0:1;
end;
(for a,b,c being (Element of A) holds ( G . (a,c) ) <= ( ( G . (a,b) ) + ( G . (b,c) ) ))
proof
let a being (Element of A),b being (Element of A),c being (Element of A);
( G . (a,c) ) <= ( ( G . (b,a) ) + ( G . (b,c) ) ) by A3;
hence thesis by A4;
end;
then G is  Reflexive  discerning  symmetric  triangle by A2,A4,METRIC_1:def 4,METRIC_1:def 5;
hence thesis by CKB3:1;
end;
(G is_metric_of A implies (G is  Reflexive  discerning & (for a,b,c being (Element of A) holds ( G . (b,c) ) <= ( ( G . (a,b) ) + ( G . (a,c) ) ))))
proof
assume A6: G is_metric_of A;
then A7: G is  Reflexive  discerning  symmetric  triangle by CKB3:1;
now
let a being (Element of A),b being (Element of A),c being (Element of A);
( G . (b,c) ) <= ( ( G . (b,a) ) + ( G . (a,c) ) ) by A7,METRIC_1:def 5;
hence ( G . (b,c) ) <= ( ( G . (a,b) ) + ( G . (a,c) ) ) by A7,METRIC_1:def 4;
end;
hence thesis by A6,CKB3:1;
end;
hence thesis by A1;
end;
